headline: Nvidia Faces New Rival As DataPelago Launches Nucleus Engine That Runs 38.6x Faster On Hash Joins And Promises Hardware Neutrality
summary: In a time when Nvidia (NASDAQ:NVDA) dominates graphics processing unit-accelerated data, a challenger has just turned the tables. DataPelago announced last week that its Nucleus universal engine outperformed Nvidia's GPU-accelerated DataFrame library cuDF by wide margins, raising the roofline of GPU-accelerated data processing and transforming the economics of artificial intelligence infrastructure. Don't Miss: The same firms that backed Uber, Venmo and eBay are investing in this pre-IPO company
